From the manufacturer

Henry Xtra

- Xtra Features

- Perfect for Pets

- Huge Capacity

- Powerful Cleaning

- Emptying with No Dust and No Mess

Xtra Features

All the features of the Henry you know and love, plus more! Henry Xtra’s unique AiroBrush is perfect for picking-up stubborn pet hairs from carpets, and his hard-floor tool is engineered to provide peak suction performance on hard-floors. With his huge 9L capacity, Henry Xtra keeps you cleaning for longer.

Specialist Hard Floor Tool

Lightweight, powerful in use, and engineered to provide peak suction performance on hard-floors, including laminate,

tiles and wood.

Perfect for Pets

Henry Xtra’s AiroBrush easily picks-up stubborn pet hairs from carpets and stairs. The AiroBrush uses Henry’s powerful airflow to operate the turbo brush, actively lifting hairs from the carpet fibres.

Up to x5 Bigger

Less emptying with a capacity up to x5 bigger than many bagless vacuums.

Emptying with No Dust and No Mess

Henry’s innovative self-seal tab locks all the dust in the bag, meaning emptying with no dust and no mess.

Powerful Cleaning

Powerful, efficient and long-life cleaning technology.

Ultimate All-rounder

Carpets, hard-floors, cars, stairs, DIY… nothing beats a Henry for versatility.

Stores Neatly Away

On-board tool storage means tools are always to hand and neatly packed away.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

sunkinthesand
5.0 out of 5 stars We should have bought one years ago. Better than any other brand we tried
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 31 March 2024
Style Name: Vacuum CleanerVerified Purchase
Many moons ago my wife and i had both done cleaning jobs and always used Henrys. They were always great but i kind of forgot how good they were. Fast forward a few years we've had dyson and numerous other brands that have been ok, but not great in a carpet floor house with dogs. Battery ones run out of power on no time and the cord ones always got clogged.

The Mrs saw Henry on sale so we decided to pick one up. Both of us now do the vacuuming with a smile on our faces. This is such a good little machine. It uses a cord so no need to worry about batteries ( there's also a nice wind up mechanism that takes seconds and works very well).
It's powerful and has a few different heads. It sucks up dog hair and debris (destroyed tennis balls) easily and doesn't clog.
It's small and low down so you can pull it round the house easily, even my elderly mother can use this easily.
There's a bag so emptying doesn't create a dust cloud and can be swapped out easily or just empty the bag if you want.
It doesn't use a huge amount of electric which is great for bills.
It's bright red so o see it a mile away and don't trip over it.

Excellent quality, highly recommended. Good value too. These vacuums last for years and are fraction of the price of the likes of Dyson and work better. Thank you for reading my review. I hope you found it useful

Marcy C
5.0 out of 5 stars I don't know why I didn't switch to Henry years ago
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 5 August 2023
Style Name: Vacuum CleanerVerified Purchase
I've pushed against getting a Henry for years - I've always been a fan of Dyson, and more recently their cordless cleaners. But I was getting bored of my Dyson clogging up too quickly and then having to wait for the filter to dry after washing it. Henry has none of these problems - he pretty much sucks everything up (and the suction power is so much better than I'd anticipated) and because everything goes into a bag, I don't get a cloud of dust blowing in my face when I empty it, or have to shove my hands in a pile of dust to unclog it. The attachments are great - I can easily get into the corners of my curved staircase. It's also got a long cable so I don't have to unplug it as I'm going upstairs. The only 'downside' is that I have to carry him up the stairs with me as I go because the nozzle isn't long enough to reach all the way up my stairs (and actually, I wouldn't want it to be because it would make it cumbersome to move around and store) but he's not that heavy. A great little vacuum cleaner at a great price. Totally recommended even if you're a die-hard Dyson fan.
